quarters location london england imprints hodder  stoughton coronet hodder faith john murray mulholland quercus saltyard sceptre two roads official website hoddercouk hodder  stoughton is a british publishing house now an imprint of hachette contents  history  early history  the postwar years  the st century  nonfiction and imprints  flipback  imprints  notable publications  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit early historyedit the firm has its origins in the s with matthew hodders employment aged fourteen with messrs jackson and walford the official publisher for the congregational union in  the firm became jackson walford and hodder but in  jackson and walford retired and thomas wilberforce stoughton joined the firm creating hodder  stoughton hodder  stoughton published both religious and secular works and its religious list contained some progressive titles these included george adam smiths isaiah for its expositor’s bible series which was one of the earliest texts to identify multiple authorship in the book of isaiah there was also a sympathetic life of st francis by paul sabatier a french protestant pastor matthew hodder made frequent visits to north america meeting with the moody press and making links with scribners and fleming h revell the secular list only gradually accepted fiction and it was still subject to moral censorship in the early part of the twentieth century matthew hodder was doubtful about the rubaiyat of omar khayyam and the company refused michael arlens the green hat a novel published by collins in  in  hodder and stoughton published an edition of lewis carrolls alices adventures in wonderland which was likely very controversial at the time given the fantastical nature of the workcitation needed the s brought an explosion of commercial fiction at keen prices  hodders yellow jackets series were the precursors of the first paperbacks and included bestsellers from john buchan edgar wallace dornford yates and sappers bulldog drummond in  the company became the exclusive british hardback publisher of leslie charteriss adventure novel series the saint publishing all  uk first editions of the series until  in this decade they also took over ownership of the medical journal the lancet hodder  stoughton were also the originators of the teach yourself line of selfinstruction books which are still published through hodder headlines educational division as the company expanded at home and overseas hodder  stoughtons list swelled to include the real life adventures in pearys north pole and several works by winston churchill during the war ralph hodder williams set up the brockhampton book co to sell off overstocks of theological works the manager ernest roker had an interest in childrens books and managed to persuade author enid blyton to write a series of books for them about four children and a dog in  the famous five series was born with five on a treasure island in  brockhampton took over the childrens writer elinor lyon whose novels the parent company had introduced in citation needed hodder  stoughton also published the biggles books by captain w e johns after he moved publishers from the oxford university press during the second world war hodder  stoughton published their first original biggles book in  with biggles sweeps the desert around septoct of that yearthey had previously published a reprint of biggles flies east in may  and the brockhampton press published johns gimlet books from  from  brockhampton press would also publish biggles books alternating with hodder  stoughton and captain w e johns remained with them until his death in  with the last hodder  stoughton biggles book appearing in august  and the last brockhampton press biggles book appearing in july  hodder  stoughton also published some of johns worrals books hodder  stoughton eventually published  biggles first editions and brockhampton press published a further  biggles first editions the postwar yearsedit this section does not cite any sources please help improve this section by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed july  learn how and when to remove this template message in  they published sir john hunts successful the ascent of everest and began their long association with thriller writer john creasey in the s they brought the knight and coronet imprints into common use the latter is particularly memorable for david nivens muchcelebrated autobiography the moons a balloon in the s the hodder and stoughton fiction list broadened to include many quality commercial authors including mary stewart whose works included madam will you talk and sold millions of copies worldwide the nonfiction publishing included anthony sampsons eradefining the anatomy of britain in  another notable title in the childrens sphere was the  brockhampton press publication of asterix the gaul by goscinny and uderzo in  john le carré’s tinker tailor soldier spy was published to much critical acclaim earning him a literary guild choice the following year previous employee john attenborough published a living memory of hodder in  the company acquired the new english library an imprint created by the american times mirror company that published works from several genres including fantasy science fiction and suspense and included books by james herbert and stephen king in  hodder  stoughton introduced sceptre as a literary imprint to sit alongside massmarket imprints coronet and nel originally publishing in paperback only early books on the sceptre list included thomas keneally’s schindler’s ark which had won the booker prize in  hodder  stoughton also won the booker prize in  with the publication of keri hulme’s the bone people originally acquired from its new zealand office other notable books on the hodder  stoughton list in this decade include rosamunde pilcher’s the shell seekers elizabeth george’s a great deliverance and the first novel in jean m auel’s prehistoric fiction series earth’s children® the clan of the cave bear which was an international success and the series completed with the publication of the land of painted caves in  has sold over  million copies worldwide in  headline bought hodder  stoughton and the company became a division of hodder headline ltd in  sceptre published charles frazier’s cold mountain and the following year hodder  stoughton released sir alex ferguson’s muchlauded autobiography managing my life in  hodder headline was acquired by w h smith the st centuryedit in  hodder headline ltd acquired john murray and two years later hodder headline was bought by hachette livre which already owned british publishers orion and octopus when hachette also acquired time warner book group now little brown it became the uk’s lead publisher the hodder  stoughton fiction list is now home to john connolly jeffery deaver john grisham sophie hannah stephen king jodi picoult peter robinson and robyn young the  publication of david nicholls’ one day heralded another international success david wrote the screenplay for the  film adaptation directed by lone scherfig and the book has sold over two million copies worldwide on  july  they released stephen kings under the dome with four cover versions in  jeffery deaver continued the james bond literary franchise with his  novel carte blanche in  hodder acquired the independent publisher quercus nonfiction and imprintsedit the nonfiction list covers many areas including biography memoir sport humour health cookery and lifestyle notable publications of recent years include james bowens a street cat named bob  its second book the world according to bob and its third book in the works michael parkinson’s parky michael caine’s the elephant to hollywood peter kay’s the book that’s more than just a bookbook and lady gaga’s first official book gaga in  sceptre continues to add to its literary heritage publishing authors such as melvyn bragg chris cleave author of the other hand jill dawson siri hustvedt thomas keneally andrew miller and david mitchell in  hodder  stoughton launched the lifestyle imprint saltyard and brought coronet back into use in  hodder and stoughton launched the imprints two roads books and mulholland books hodder faith is the uk’s leading christian publisher home to authors philip yancey joyce meyer and rt kendell amongst others they continue to publish the niv bible in its various formats and to break new ground with books like wm paul young’s the shack  flipbackedit in  hodder launched a wholly new print format for books the flipback printed on bible paper and designed to replicate the traditional print reading experience in an edition not much bigger than an iphone imprintsedit coronet books hodder faith hodder moa beckett new zealand hodder  stoughton john murray mulholland quercus sceptre saltyard two roads yellow kite notable publicationsedit  natural law in the spiritual world  henry drummund  from log cabin to white house  william thayer  the personal life of queen victoria  sarah tooley  peter pan and wendy  jm barrie the lord kitchener memorial book sir hedley le bas editor   collected verse  rudyard kipling  goodbye mr chips  james hilton  oliver cromwell  john buchan  the queens book of the red cross  five on a treasure island  enid blyton  biggles sweeps the desert captain w e johns  green dolphin country  elizabeth goudge  the colditz story  p r reid  the ascent of everest  john hunt  katharine  anya seton  the ipcress file len deighton  the anatomy of britain  anthony sampson  asterix the gaul  goscinny and uderzo  love story  erich segal  the moons a balloon  david niven  tinker tailor soldier spy  john le carré  the clan of the cave bear  jean m auel  schindlers ark  thomas keneally  the bone people  keri hulme  the shell seekers  rosamund pilcher  a great deliverance  elizabeth george  cold mountain  charles frazier  managing my life  alex ferguson  kylie la la la  kylie minogue  william baker  my sisters keeper  jodi picoult  my booky wook  russell brand  the other hand  chris cleave  one day  david nicholls  under the dome  stephen king  a street cat named bob  james bowen  the land of painted caves  jean auel  the litigators  john grisham  playing it my way  sachin tendulkar   things successful people do  nigel cumberland see alsoedit childrens literature portal list of largest uk book publishers referencesedit  four covers for under the domes uk paperback release  hodder buys quercus  book  print in new zealand a guide to print culture in aotearoa  history new zealand electronic text centre victoria university of wellington  retrieved september     le bas hedley ed the lord kitchener memorial book hodder  stoughton  further readingedit attenborough john  a living memory hodder and stoughton  london hodder and stoughton bennett bryan  hamilton anthony  edward arnold  years of publishing illustrated with black and white plates including a frontispiece of edward arnold london edward arnold a division of hodder  stoughton isbn  external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to hodder  stoughton official website flipback books v t e lagardère sca lagardère publishing hachette livre armand colin calmannlévy dalloz fayard gautierlanguereau grasset hachette hatier larousse librairie générale française  jc lattès pika stock hatier edelsa hachette usa black dog  leventhal center street faithwords grand central hyperion little brown mulholland books orbit yen  hachette uk hachette childrens orchard books franklin watts wayland headline hodder  stoughton coronet hodder faith mulholland quercus sceptre two roads yellow kite hodder education chambers galore park gibson philip allan updates teach yourself john murray little brown constable  robinson orbit virago sphere octopus cassell illustrated conran octopus gaia godsfield hamlyn mitchell beazley philips spruce orion books weidenfeld  nicolson gollancz lagardère active hachette filipacchi elle